Module kivakit.core
Package com.telenav.kivakit.core.collections.list

Class BaseList<Value>

java.lang.Object
com.telenav.kivakit.core.collections.BaseCollection<Value>
com.telenav.kivakit.core.collections.list.BaseList<Value>
All Implemented Interfaces:
Countable, Addable<Value>, Appendable<Value>, Copyable<Value,BaseList<Value>>, Emptiness, Indexable<Value>, Joinable<Value>, Prependable<Value>, Sectionable<Value,BaseList<Value>>, Sequence<Value>, Sized, SpaceLimited, Factory<BaseList<Value>>, Zeroable, AsString, StringFormattable, Iterable<Value>, Collection<Value>, List<Value>, RandomAccess
Direct Known Subclasses:
ObjectList
public abstract class BaseList<Value> extends BaseCollection<Value> implements Appendable<Value>, Copyable<Value,BaseList<Value>>, Indexable<Value>, List<Value>, Prependable<Value>, RandomAccess, Sectionable<Value,BaseList<Value>>
A base class for bounded lists which adds convenient methods as well as support for various KivaKit interfaces:
  • Appendable
  • Copyable
  • Indexable
  • List
  • Prependable
  • RandomAccess
  • Sectionable

Functional Methods

Some methods are functional and return a new list. The method newList() is used to create lists. Subclasses create the subclass list type by overriding onNewList().

  • copy() - A copy of this list
  • Copyable.without(Matcher) - This list without the matching elements
  • first(int) - A new list with the first n elements in it
  • first(Count) - A new list with the first n elements in it
  • last(int) - A new list with the first n elements in it
  • last(Count) - A new list with the first n elements in it
  • leftOf(int) - The elements in this list to the left on the given index, exclusive
  • rightOf(int) - The elements in this list to the right on the given index, exclusive
  • Copyable.matching(Matcher) - A copy of this list filtered to matching elements
  • BaseCollection.map(Function) - A copy of this list with elements mapped to another type
  • BaseCollection.sorted()
  • BaseCollection.sorted(Comparator)
  • reversed() - This list reversed
  • maybeReversed(boolean) - This list reversed if the given boolean is true
  • uniqued()
  • BaseCollection.with(Object)
  • Copyable.without(Matcher)
